7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. R.S. 40:2009.10.2 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 §2009.10.2. One-star nursing facilities; state requirements
10 A. The legislature hereby finds the following:
11 (1) The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services created the
12 Five-Star Quality Rating System to help consumers, families, and caregivers
13 compare nursing homes more easily and to help identify areas about which they
14 may want to ask questions. Nursing homes with five stars are considered to have
15 the highest quality and nursing homes with one star are considered to have the
16 lowest quality as compared with other nursing homes. There is one overall
17 five-star rating for each nursing home and separate ratings for health
