2 (2) The office of adult and aging services within the Louisiana
3 Department of Health offers home- and community-based services to help older
4 adults and individuals with adult-onset disabilities maintain their independence,
5 including the Adult Day Health Care Waiver, Community Choices Waiver,
6 Long-Term Personal Care Services, and Program of All-Inclusive Care for the
7 Elderly.
8 (3) The Community Choices Waiver is a home- and community-based
9 service that serves older adults and persons with adult-onset disabilities. The
10 Community Choices Waiver contains a wide array of services, including
11 support coordination, nursing and skilled therapy assessments and services,
12 in-home monitoring systems, home modifications and assistive technologies,
13 personal care, home-delivered meals, monitored in-home caregiving, and
14 caregiver respite.
15 B. If any nursing home receives an overall quality rating of one star on
16 the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services rating scale, every resident or
17 potential resident of the nursing home and their families or legal guardian shall
18 receive individual counseling by an office of aging and adult services' employee
19 to explain the quality rating scale and to offer the below options:
20 (1) Immediate access to a Community Choices Waiver and any other
21 home- and community-based service for which the individual is eligible in order
22 to receive comprehensive services in the community in lieu of the nursing home.
23 (2) Immediate transfer to another available nursing home of their choice
24 that rated an overall two or above on the quality rating scale.
25 C. Any potential resident and all placing entities shall be notified of the
26 one-star rating of the nursing home prior to placement so that other options
27 may be presented before an individual is placed in the nursing home. Prior to
28 admission, the potential resident and the resident's family or legal guardian
29 shall be counseled by an office of aging and adult services' employee to explore
