Proposed law further requires the office to offer the resident or potential resident either
immediate access to a Community Choices Waiver and any other home- and
community-based service or immediate transfer to a nursing home of their choice that is
rated an overall two or above.
Proposed law requires potential residents and placing entities to be notified of the one-star
rating prior to placement.
Proposed law requires the administrator of a nursing home that has been assigned a one-star
rating to submit a remediation plan to the La. Dept. of Health within 30 days after receiving
the rating.
Proposed law provides that any nursing home with an overall one-star rating may be subject
to additional surveys, monitoring, and intervention by the La. Dept. of Health.
Proposed law provides that if a nursing home has not improved its overall rating after a
two-year period, the department shall enforce sanctions up to and including placing the
nursing home on a closure track.
Proposed law provides that proposed law applies to any nursing home with an overall quality
rating of one-star on Oct. 1, 2026, and shall remain effective until the rating has improved
to a quality rating of two stars or higher.
Proposed law provides that proposed law may be known and shall be cited as the "Nursing
Home Choice Act".
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 40:2009.10.2)
